Antennae at same level of pseudorostral spines. Antennules completely retractable in deep fossae. Basal antennal article fused to carapace, slightly curved, with smooth flattened surface, slightly rounded external distal angle; distinct tubercle at base of basal antennal article (
Fig. 5B
). Squarish epistome. Pterygostomial region enlarged into plate with rounded edge (
Fig. 5B
). Buccal frame totally covered by third maxillipeds when closed.

Male thoracic sternum anteriorly depressed, sternites 1–3 fused (
Fig. 5B
). Male abdomen with triangular telson and 6 free somites (
Fig. 5B
). G1 straight with flattened tip (
Fig. 6
).
